title: Grateful Dead Live at Richmond Coliseum on 1983-10-08
description:
Set 1: Feel Like A Stranger, Friend Of The Devil, Minglewood Blues, Brown Eyed Women, Cassidy, West L.A. Fadeaway, Hell In A Bucket > Deal

Set 2: Day Job > Playing In The Band > Crazy Fingers > Drums > Truckin' > Spoonful > Wharf Rat > Good Lovin'

E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Crazy, crazy recording! ok, so this is one of those audience tapes that most of us remembering having in our collections  The kind that really captures the feeling of the show, and that has an irresistible wigged-out imbalance of one kind or another (e.g., Brent being louder than Jerry for a song or two). Now, in truth, I haven't compared it to any of the other 10-8-83 recordings, so it may just turn out that this is the way the sound was mixed that night.  But if you want to have some fun, download this show, burn a cd, or upload to your mp3, and take a drive, or a run, listening to it a just above normal volume.   The 'Stranger' alone is worth the listen.
